# Accessibility & Inclusivity

Sources: Elastic Docs Style Guide, Google Developer Documentation Style Guide

## Images and Media

- Every image **must** have descriptive alt text that conveys the information the image provides.
- Alt text for diagrams should describe what the diagram shows, not just its title.
- Screenshots of terminal output should be accompanied by a text-based code block with the same content.

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
![](pipeline.png)

<!-- GOOD -->
![Data flow from global memory through TMA into shared memory tiles](pipeline.png)
```

## Inclusive Language

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| blacklist / whitelist | blocklist / allowlist |
| master / slave | primary / replica, leader / follower |
| sanity check | quick check, smoke test, validation |
| dummy | placeholder, sample |
| he / she (generic) | they |
| man-hours | person-hours, engineering hours |
| crippled | degraded, limited |

## Device-Agnostic Instructions

- Use **"select"** instead of "click" (works for mouse, touch, keyboard).
- Use **"enter"** instead of "type" when describing text input.
- Use **"press"** for keyboard shortcuts: "Press `Ctrl+S`."

## Directional Language

- Avoid "above", "below", "left", "right" — the layout may differ on mobile, RTL languages, or screen readers.
- Use "previous", "following", "earlier in this section" instead.

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
As shown in the diagram above…
See the table on the right.

<!-- GOOD -->
As shown in the preceding diagram…
See the following table.
```

## Links

- Link text must describe the destination — never use "click here" or "this link".

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
For more info, click [here](memory.md).

<!-- GOOD -->
For details, see [Memory model in Choreo](memory.md).
```
